'''空軍二號'''（{{lang-en|'''Air Force Two'''}}），是任何接載着[[美国副总统|美国副总统]]的[[空軍|空軍]][[飛機|飛機]]的[[航空|航空]][[無線電台呼號|無線電台呼號]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.af.mil/factsheets/factsheet.asp?id=90 |title=Factsheets: C-32 |accessdate=2009-01-30 |work=Air Force Link |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080803093535/http://www.af.mil/factsheets/factsheet.asp?id=90 |archivedate=2008年8月3日 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.faa.gov/air_traffic/publications/atpubs/ATC/atc0204.html| title = Order 7110.65R (Air Traffic Control) §2-4-20 ¶7| accessdate = 2007-08-27| date = 14 March 2007| publisher = Federal Aviation Administration| archive-date = 2009-10-12| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20091012042224/http://www.faa.gov/air_traffic/publications/atpubs/ATC/atc0204.html| dead-url = no}}</ref>。目前美國副總統最常用的是一架[[波音C-32|波音C-32]]飛機（[[波音757|波音757]]的改裝版）。其他曾使用的飛機型號包括：{{link-en|波音C-40剪刀|Boeing C-40 Clipper}}、{{link-en|灣流III|Gulfstream III}}、{{link-en|灣流V|Gulfstream V}}和[[灣流G550|灣流G550]]等等<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2002/03/10/cheney.htm |work=USA Today |title=Cheney heads overseas to talk terrorism |accessdate=2009-01-30 |date=10 March 2002 |publisher=Associated Press |archive-date=2011-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110526213046/http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2002/03/10/cheney.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.usnews.com/usnews/news/articles/cheneytrip/notebook_311.htm |work=US News |title=Reporter's Notebook on Cheney's Mideast trip: Day 1: London |last=Whitelaw |first=Kevin |date=11 March 2002 |accessdate=2009-01-30 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090113154817/http://www.usnews.com/usnews/news/articles/cheneytrip/notebook_311.htm |archivedate=2009年1月13日 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

==傳聞==
有謠言指出美國副總統是不能與[[美国总统|總統]]搭同一趟班機的，但事實上是沒有明文規定。只是總統和副總統各有大量人力物力支援，讓總統跟副總統乘坐同一班機是不合乎經濟邏輯和無需要的。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vaFnlW5zCZs |title=Does The President Really Need Air Force One? @2:04 |accessdate=2016-12-01 |archive-date=2020-11-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201120094106/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vaFnlW5zCZs |dead-url=no }}</ref>

